purpose: TypeScript declaration file that provides type definitions for Vite's client-side APIs and environment variables
key_points: This is a standard Vite environment type declaration file
It references Vite's built-in client types
Enables TypeScript to understand Vite-specific globals and modules
Typically auto-generated when creating a Vite project with TypeScript

patterns: Triple-slash directive pattern for TypeScript type references
issues: File is minimal - may need to extend with custom environment variable types if the project uses them
Could add interface declarations for import.meta.env if custom environment variables are used
